Description: 31 fragments of papyrus, mostly very small, extracted from cartonnage with Demotic and Greek (mainly) texts, in some cases, on both sides.
Curator's comments: Only three of the demotic fragments contain more than a few signs. Of these, two belong to accounts. The other (top right-hand corner), which is a narow strip with part of 17 lines on the recto and and 11 on the verso, may be part of a letter (probable use of interrogative marker, text in 2nd person singular).
